  "prompt": "The resultant of two forces has magnitude 20N. One of the forces has magnitude 20\u221a3N making an angle of 30\u00b0 with the resultant? What is the magnitude of the other force?",
  "response": "To determine the magnitude of the other force, let's analyze the given information step by step.\n\n### Given:\n- The resultant force \\( R \\) has a magnitude of **20 N**.\n- One of the forces \\( F_1 \\) has a magnitude of \\( 20\\sqrt{3} \\) N and makes an angle of **30\u00b0** with the resultant \\( R \\).\n\n### Objective:\nFind the magnitude of the second force \\( F_2 \\).\n\n### Approach:\n\n1. **Vector Representation:**\n   - Assume the resultant \\( R \\) lies along the positive \\( x \\)-axis.\n   - The force \\( F_1 \\) makes a 30\u00b0 angle with \\( R \\).\n\n2. **Components of \\( F_1 \\):**\n   - \\( F_{1x} = F_1 \\cos(30\u00b0) = 20\\sqrt{3} \\times \\frac{\\sqrt{3}}{2} = 30 \\) N\n   - \\( F_{1y} = F_1 \\sin(30\u00b0) = 20\\sqrt{3} \\times \\frac{1}{2} = 10\\sqrt{3} \\) N\n\n3. **Resultant Force Components:**\n   - Since \\( R \\) is purely along the \\( x \\)-axis:\n     - \\( R_x = 20 \\) N\n     - \\( R_y = 0 \\) N\n\n4. **Components of \\( F_2 \\):**\n   - \\( F_{2x} = R_x - F_{1x} = 20 - 30 = -10 \\) N\n   - \\( F_{2y} = R_y - F_{1y} = 0 - 10\\sqrt{3} = -10\\sqrt{3} \\) N\n\n5. **Magnitude of \\( F_2 \\):**\n   \\[\n   |F_2| = \\sqrt{F_{2x}^2 + F_{2y}^2} = \\sqrt{(-10)^2 + (-10\\sqrt{3})^2} = \\sqrt{100 + 300} = \\sqrt{400} = 20 \\text{ N}\n   \\]\n\n### Conclusion:\nThe magnitude of the other force \\( F_2 \\) is **20 N**.\n\n**Answer:**  \nThe magnitude of the other force is\u202f20\u202fN.",
